<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Blue is the young(est?) colour - and very NES:y.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16053&amp;p=197781#p197781"><![CDATA[
Sapir-Whorf in a nutshell:<br />If a language lacks a word for blue, its speakers will pay less attention to whether something is blue because it isn't something they'll need to repeat to someone else.<br /><br /><img src="https://static.miraheze.org/allthetropeswiki/thumb/7/7e/Sapir-Worf_hypothesis.jpg/320px-Sapir-Worf_hypothesis.jpg" alt="Image" /><br />Sapir-<em>Worf</em>, on the other hand:<br /><a href="http://klingonska.org/ref/color.html" class="postlink">Klingon basic color names</a> are <a href="https://allthetropes.org/wiki/Orange-Blue_Contrast" class="postlink">orange and blue</a>, with idiomatic use of &quot;more&quot; and &quot;bright&quot; to mean &quot;one or two steps higher in the rainbow&quot;.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Jun 08, 2017 10:57 am</p><hr />
