I'm going to assume the concept is just lost in translation on you, Bregalad.<br /><br />The point, however, is that <em>linguistically</em>, &quot;blue&quot; is one of the later colors to be named, chronologically.  Hence the <em>concept</em> of blue is young <em>in English</em>.<br /><br />Read <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linguistic_relativity_and_the_color_naming_debate" class="postlink">wikipedia:Linguistic relativity and the color naming debate</a> for some background.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Wed Jun 07, 2017 11:46 pm</p><hr />
